# CLAUDE.md

This file guides Claude Code when working in this repository. It was generated by the `code-new-project` skill against Tyler's default app stack — see that skill's `reference.md` for the full rationale behind each choice below.

## Stack

- Frontend: {{FRONTEND}}
- Backend: Rust + Axum + sqlx (`backend/`)
- RPC: Connect-RPC for unary/server-streaming (`proto/`, see `backend/CONNECT_RPC_NOTE.md` for current maturity status), WebSocket for bidirectional streaming (`backend/api/src/ws.rs`)
- Compute: GCP Cloud Run (`iac/cloud_run.tf`)
- Data: Neon Postgres (`iac/neon.tf`) + Cloudflare R2 (`iac/r2.tf`)
- IaC: OpenTofu (`iac/`)
- CI: GitHub Actions, path-filtered by directory (`.github/workflows/ci.yml`)

## Development Workflow

**Planning and implementing features**: use `/sdd:full` (or the individual phases — `/sdd:1-ideate`, `/sdd:2-research`, `/sdd:3-plan`, `/sdd:4-validate`, `/sdd:5-implement`, `/sdd:6-verify`, `/sdd:7-ship`) rather than implementing ad hoc. It runs ideation → research → architecture planning (with ADRs) → test-plan validation → subagent-driven implementation → review → ship, and produces durable artifacts in `docs/tasks/` along the way. Use `/sdd:quick` instead for small bug fixes that don't need the full ceremony.

**Documenting what the app does**: use `journeys-extract` to derive `docs/journeys/*.md` spec files (one per user journey, with stable `journey_id`s and test linkage fields) from the current code — this is the source of truth for "what features does this app have and how do they work," not scattered comments or tribal knowledge. Use `journeys-enrich` to deepen a draft journey and link tests, and `journeys-verify` periodically to catch drift between the docs and what the code actually does. Re-run `journeys-extract` after major feature additions rather than hand-writing journey docs.

**Establishing the project's brand/positioning**: before (or early alongside) building user-facing surfaces, run the `pm-brand-strategy` skill to set the project's marketing/brand direction — voice, audience, positioning. It writes `.claude/product-marketing-context.md`, which other brand/design/UX skills read automatically. Do this once at project start; revisit only on a deliberate pivot.

## Architecture Notes

- Axum has no framework-level architectural guardrails (unlike Spring Boot) — structure is enforced by convention, not the framework. Follow the module layout already established in `backend/api/src/`: `routes/` for thin handlers, `db/` for sqlx queries only, `domain/` for business logic with no framework types leaking in.
- Cloud Run injects `$PORT` — the backend must bind to it, never hardcode a port (already handled in `main.rs`).
- IaC (`iac/*.tf`) has `TODO`-gated variables with no defaults on purpose — an unconfigured `tofu apply` should fail loudly, not provision into the wrong project.
- If this project is a Firebase migration, see `AUTH.md`/`SYNC.md` for the Ory Kratos/PowerSync composition instead of adopting a new bundled BaaS.

